    public static final String phq9FirstPara = "The PHQ-9 is a self-administered questionnaire commonly used to assess the presence and severity of depressive symptoms. It's based on the diagnostic criteria for major depressive disorder from the DSM-IV.";
    public static final String phq9SecondPara = "Consisting of 9 questions, the PHQ-9 scores range from 0 to 27, reflecting the frequency of symptoms. It's an essential tool for clinicians to screen, diagnose, monitor, and measure the severity of depression, aiding in personalized treatment planning.";
    public static final String phq9ThirdPara = "The original measure was developed by Drs. Robert L. Spitzer, Janet B.W. Williams, Kurt Kroenke and colleagues, with an educational grant from Pfizer Inc. No permission required to reproduce, translate, display or distribute.";
    public static final String gad7FirstPara = "The GAD-7 is a widely used self-reporting tool that measures the severity of generalized anxiety disorder (GAD) symptoms. It’s designed to identify the frequency and intensity of anxiety-related concerns.";
    public static final String gad7SecondPara = "Comprising 7 questions, the GAD-7 scores range from 0 to 21, with higher scores indicating more severe anxiety symptoms. It serves as an efficient screening tool and severity measure for anxiety disorders, assisting healthcare providers in individualized care and monitoring.";
    public static final String gad7ThirdPara = "The original measure was developed by Drs. Robert L. Spitzer, Janet B.W. Williams, Kurt Kroenke and colleagues, with an educational grant from Pfizer Inc. No permission required to reproduce, translate, display or distribute.";
    public static final String dass21FirstPara = "The DASS-21 (Depression, Anxiety, and Stress Scale) is a self-report tool, specifically crafted to measure and detect the emotional states of depression, anxiety, and notably stress. Its design allows for a nuanced understanding of an individual’s stress levels, along with other emotional states.";
    public static final String dass21SecondPara = "Consisting of 21 questions, including a dedicated stress sub-scale, the DASS-21 is renowned for its ability to pinpoint stress severity. It’s a valuable tool for identifying and quantifying emotional distress, enabling healthcare and wellness professionals to craft targeted interventions and support.";
    public static final String dass21ThirdPara = "The original measure was developed by Lovibond, S.H. & Lovibond, P.F. (1995), Manual for the Depression Anxiety Stress Scales. (2nd. Ed.). No permission required to reproduce, translate, display or distribute.";
    public static final String casFirstPara = "The Clinical Anger Scale is a self-administered questionnaire that stands as a pivotal instrument for assessing and quantifying the severity of anger-related emotions and behaviors.";
    public static final String casSecondPara = "Consisting of 21 questions, the CAS scores range from 0 to 63. This scale empowers mental health professionals and individuals alike to effectively gauge and address anger-related issues. It serves as an indispensable resource for precise evaluation, intervention, and treatment planning.";
    public static final String casThirdPara = "Snell, W. E., Jr., Gum, S., Shuck, R. L., Mosley, J. A., & Kite, T. L. (1995). The clinical anger scale: Preliminary reliability and validity. Journal of Clinical Psychology, 51(2), 215-226.";
    public static final String ohqFirstPara = "The Oxford Happiness Questionnaire is a well-established psychological assessment tool designed to measure an individual’s subjective well-being and happiness levels. It consists of a series of questions that respondents answer based on their feelings and experiences.";
    public static final String ohqSecondPara = "It is widely used for gauging personal happiness and life satisfaction. Its comprehensive approach allows individuals, therapists, and researchers to delve deep into the science of happiness and devise strategies to enhance overall life contentment.";
